    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>Corrections</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Correction of June 2 article on performance by New York fourth graders on statewide reading test</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>An article on Friday about fourth graders' performance on a statewide reading test misidentified the New York City district in which scores rose most sharply. It was District 33, a citywide unit with 3 elementary schools and 10 middle schools reporting to the chancellor rather than to a community school board; it was not District 31 on Staten Island.</p>
        <p>A chart with the article misstated the improvement in Irvington, N.Y., since 1999. It was 4 percentage points, not 14.</p>
      </block>
